1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,020
All the data gathering is the first step of a Data Wrangler workflow.

2
00:00:04,020 --> 00:00:08,370
It can actually be incredibly complicated in order to get the data that you need,

3
00:00:08,370 --> 00:00:10,500
and involves a number of different steps that you'll

4
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:13,035
need to identify as part of your workflows.

5
00:00:13,035 --> 00:00:16,575
Why? Well, even if you're only working with files on hand,

6
00:00:16,575 --> 00:00:20,325
you may have multiple data files from different sources,

7
00:00:20,325 --> 00:00:23,040
multiple data files from the same source,

8
00:00:23,040 --> 00:00:26,160
files dedicated to explain the variables in your data,

9
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:29,325
sometimes known as data dictionaries, and more.

10
00:00:29,325 --> 00:00:32,600
Zip files, and.tar.gz files

11
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:35,630
for Unix systems are a popular way to compress multiple files,

12
00:00:35,630 --> 00:00:37,915
and are useful for data gathering workflows.

13
00:00:37,915 --> 00:00:43,200
Being able to programmatically unzip files is great for reproducible data workflows.

14
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:48,140
So another analyst doesn't have to perform many manual steps when reproducing your work.

15
00:00:48,140 --> 00:00:52,340
Let's now take a look at how to programmatically unzip the file via Python.

16
00:00:52,340 --> 00:00:54,920
Let's take a brief look at how to programmatically

17
00:00:54,920 --> 00:00:58,390
unzip files with Python using the zip file module.

18
00:00:58,390 --> 00:01:01,520
First, we start with importing the zip file module.

19
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:05,465
Then we're using a Python Context Manager to open the zip file,

20
00:01:05,465 --> 00:01:10,415
which is a popular way in Python to efficiently manage resources that your programs need.

21
00:01:10,415 --> 00:01:15,880
The width statement opens a zip file called file.zip in read mode,

22
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:19,370
and creates a zip file object called a zip_ref.

23
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:23,900
Then the extract all method is called on the zip_ref object to

24
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:29,310
extract all the files from the zip archive into a directory named targetdir.

